review_blob: Tap at the brewery. Pours black with tan head. Aroma of cocoa, espresso, hints of nuttiness. Taste is full bodied, dry, medium carbonation. Overall, very nice.

Bottle. Pours deep purple with red hues. Aroma of fresh berries, blueberry, sweet dessert. Taste is very rich, lots of berry, full bodied, sweet but not overly. Overall, the best mead that I have had. Very delicious.
Bottle. Pours yellow with minimal head. Aroma of fruity dessert, raisins, vanilla, cider, skunk, port. Taste is very port-like, very sweet, medium to full bodied, very rich. Overall, meh.

Bottle. Pours black with off-white head. Aroma of tobacco, cocoa, vanilla, dark fruits. Taste is very dry throughout, full bodied, rich, medium carbonation, Overall, nice but wish it was not quite so bone dry.
Bottle. Pours golden with white head. Aroma is strong brett, lemon, citrus, cherry. Taste is sour tart throughout, crisp, lively. Overall, nice.
beer_name: The Rare Barrel Ambassadors #4: Impossible Soul

review_blob: Bottle. Pours hazy orange with white head. Aroma of fresh peaches, a little funk, funk, wild yeast. Taste is bright fruity peach, tart throughout, long lasting flavorful finish, good carbonation. Overall, exceptional.

Bottle. Pours yellow with white head. Aroma is very strong of tropical fruits, mango, pineapple, tangerines. Taste is tart throughout with a great tropcial hoppiness, good carbonation, nice flavor, great long finish. Overall, exceptional.

Bottle Pours yellow with white head. Aroma is strong of ginger, lemon, funk, floral. Taste like a moscow mule, light to medium bodied, very flavorful. Overall, nice but tastes more like a cocktail than a beer.
Bottle. Pours red/ pink with white head. Aroma of berries, funk, wild yeast, blueberry. Taste is dry, lively, lots of funk. Overall, very nice.
Bottle. Pours black with tan head. Aroma of cocoa, tobacco, wood, molasses. Taste is full bodied, rich, long finish. Overall, very good.
Bottle. Pours amber with white head. Aroma of vinegar, figs, wood, dough, balsamic. Taste is sweet with a heavy sourness cutting through it, a medicinal. Overall, okay.

Tap. Pours hazy orange/ brown with white head. Aroma of sweet caramel, resinous hops, bread, pine. Taste is med to full bodied, med carbonation, sticky, sweet backbone with a bitter finish. Overall, ex.cep.tion.al. Sooooo delicious!
Bottle. Pours red with orangey/ brown hues and minimal white head. Aroma of citrus, cranberry, wood, funk. Taste is very acidic throughou, crisp, tart. Overall, okay.

Bottle. Pours hazy red with orange hues and white head. Aroma is very funky, cherry, spices, pie. Taste is light bodied, high carbonation, very lively, kinda like a spritzer. Overall, very neutral on this one, not bad or good.
Can. Pours brown with red hues and white head. Aroma of caramel, cereal, figs. Taste is medium bodied, crisp, med carbonation. Overall, pretty good.
Bottle. Pours orange with white head. Aroma of citrus, orange, sweet malts, caramel. Taste of med bodied, med carbonation, well balanced. Overall, okay.

Bottle. Pours clear orange with white head. Aroma is very malt forward, piney, trees, earthy, spicy. Taste is med bodied, high carbonation, bitter finish. Overall, okay, something a bit contrasting....
Tap at brewery. Pours light yellow with white head. Aroma is spicy, lager yeast. Taste is light, crisp, a bit dirty, spicy. Overall, good.
Tap at brewery. Pours clear orange with white head. Aroma is floral, spicy, pepper, grapefruit. Taste is bitter throughout, med bodied, med carb. Overall, nice.
Tap at brewery. Pours clear brown with red hues and white head. Aroma is grassy, pine, caramel, musty. Taste is med bodied, musty finish, med carbonation. Overall, not my favorite.
Tap at brewery. Pours clear brown with orange hues and white head. Aroma is strong vanilla, grain, citrus. Taste is med bodied, low carbonation, smooth. Overall, good.
Tap at brewery. Pours black with tan head. Aroma is roasty, chocolate, toast. Taste is med to full bodied, light carbonation, smooth. Overall, an excellent oatmeal stout.
Tap at brewery. Pours hazy orange with white head. Aroma is very tropical, pineapple, mango, mandarins, orange peel, . Taste is med bodied, sweet with a hop finish. Overall, nice.
Tap at brewery. Pours clear brown with red hues and white head. Aroma of cereal, grain, caramel, barley. Taste is med bodied, crisp, med carbonation. OverLl, good.

Bottle. Pours hazy deep red with minimal pink head. Aroma of fresh raspberries, pie, vanilla, hint of wood. Taste is high carbonation, lively, sour throughout, nice fruitiness. Overall, realllly like this one.

Bottle. Pours orange with white head. Aroma is strong raspberry, fruit, brett, plastic, bandaid funk. Taste is light bodied, slight vinegary, med carbonation. Overall, almost really good but just slightly too plasticy.
Bottle. Pours hazy yellow with white head. Aroma of pineapple, cloves, brett. Taste is light bodied, crisp, fruity, funky. Overall, good.
Bottle. Pours black with deep tan head. Aroma is very chocolate, funk, cherry, caramel. Taste is smooth, rich backbone with a nice sourness cutting through, medium bodied. Overall, nice.
Bottle. Pours deep brown with off-white head. Aroma is slightly pumpkiny, caramel, bread, earthy. Taste is medium bodied, bitter finish, med carbonation. Overall, not too great.
Bottle. Pours black with tan head. Aroma of chocolate, vanilla, sweet, wood. Taste is very smooth, full bodied and rich, long flavorful finish. Overall, this is exceptional, love it!

Bottle. Pours clear brown with red hues and off white head. Aroma of cherries, vanilla, cranberries, fig, lacto. Taste is lightly sour throughout, crisp, really interesting flavor combination...Overall, good.
Tap at brewery. Pours orange with white head. Aroma is strong of fir, very christmas wreathy, pine. Taste is medium bodied, crisp, high carbonation, very floral throughout. Overall, nice,

Bottle. Pours black with tan head. Aroma of chocolate, coffee, fruity. Taste is full bodied but a very watery/ thinness to it, med carbonation, creamy, smooth. Overall, good flavor but wish it wasnt so thinned out.
Tap at brewery. Pours orange with white head. Aroma is straight cat piss, ammonia. Taste is light bodied, crisp, soooo cat pee. Overall, very disgusting.

Bottle. Pours brown/ orange with pink head, very interesting color. Aroma smells very similiar to cranberry juice, brett, wood. Taste is very cranberry juice like, tart throughout, med carb, med bodied. Overall, really like this one!
Bottle. Pours deep red with pink head. Aroma of brett, elastic, cranberry, pomegranate, exotic fruits. Taste is crisp, fruity, tart fruit throughout, long dry finish. Overall, very good.
beer_name: De Garde Imperial Cran Currant Bu

review_blob: Tap at brewery. Pours red/ pink with white head. Aroma of fresh berries, jammy, fruity forward, juice. Taste is fruity, med bodied, sour throughout, crisp. Overall, juicy, sour and tasty.
Bottle Pours yellow with white head. Aroma of funk, tropical, sweet citrus., touch of wood. Taste is easy, crisp, sour throughout. Overall, pretty good.
Bottle. Pours orange with white head. Aroma of oranges, citrus, tangerines, funk, lacto. Taste is tart throughout, hop are very prominent, light bodied, simple and refreshing. Overall, pretty tasty.
Tap at brewery. Pours yellow with white head. Aroma is tropical, sweet fruits, wood, funk Taste is funky throughout with a slight sweetness on the back. Overall, very good.
Tap at brewery. Pours bright orange with white head. Aroma is extreme nectarine, jammy, fruit forward, lacto. Taste is smooth, crisp, lots of fruit, lacto. Overall, very good.
Bottle. Pours bright hazy yellow with minimal head. Aroma is stone fruit, fruity, wood, lacto. Taste is sour throughout, extreme ripe fruit coming through, med bodied. Overall, very good.
Tap at brewery. Pours red with pink tint head. Aroma is fruit forward, lots of raspberry, berry, jam, wood. Taste is med sour, crisp, juicy. Overall, very gooood!
Tap at brewery. Pours pink with white head. Aroma is very winey, grapey, cherry, wood, funk. Taste is sour, med bodied, very winey. Overall, nice.
Tap at brewery. Pours pink with white head. Aroma is cherry, vinegar, fruity. Taste is medium bodied, crisp, fruity, long sour finish. Overall, good.

Bottle. Pours bright yellow with white head. Aroma is overly ripe fruity, strong passion fruit, lots of lacto, vinegar. Taste is so acidic it is unbearable, high carbonation, lively. Overall, smells of rotten fruit with an overly acidic taste. This is horrible.
Bottle Pours yellow with white head. Aroma is smokey, herbal, vanilla, wood, lacto. Taste is med bodied, tart with a weird smokey tea thing. Overall, grosssss.
Bottle. Pours yellow with white head. Aroma is pineapple, funk, a bit of wood, earthy. Taste is crisp, an explosion of flavor, bright, light bodied. Overall, super good, I could drink this every day.

Bottle Pours pink with white head. Aroma is strong of cherry, funk, pie. Taste is light bodied, crisp, a bit less cherry flavor going on than the other Casey cherries, lively, sour throughout. Overall, delicious.
Bottle. Pours pink with white head. Aroma is cherry pie, lacto, funky. Taste is high carbonation, great cherry flavor, tart throughout, crisp. Overall, very good.
